- 'Blossoms' refers to ads;
- 'Caught the eye of more than 100 bees' refers to more than 100 clicks;
- 'Sweet nectar score' refers to an average engagement score;
- 'Full cycle of the sun' refers to the level 5 in the running total of ad performance.

- 'Engagement score above average' refers to an engagement score greater than 0.5;
- 'Significant level of interest' implies a high level of interaction, such as clicking on the ads;
- 'More than 10 different video ads' indicates a diverse set of video advertisements.

- 'North' region refers to a specific geographical area defined in the `cities` table;
- 'Average conversion rate' is calculated by dividing the total number of conversions by the count of unique ads;
- 'Clicked on ad' indicates that the user has interacted with the advertisement.

- 'seasoned travelers' refers to users who have an average session duration greater than 30 minutes;
- 'surpassed the threshold of youth' refers to users who are older than 25;
- 'profound connection with the digital realm' refers to users with an engagement score greater than 0.4 with advertisements;
- 'bustling city of '1'' refers to the city with the identifier '1'.

- "Engagement" in the context of digital marketing refers to the level of interaction a user has with an advertisement, measured by metrics such as the engagement score and time spent;
- "10 seconds" is a threshold commonly used to determine meaningful user engagement with digital content;
- "More than 10 users" is a threshold to ensure that the data is statistically significant and not influenced by outliers.

- Click-through rate (CTR) is calculated as the number of clicks divided by the number of impressions;
- The query filters cities based on a CTR of more than 10%;
- The results are ordered by the number of clicks in descending order.

- 'Shining stars of the digital sky' refers to the most popular ads;
- 'Attracted the most clicks' means the ads with the highest click count;
- 'Categories and targeting options' refer to the specific types and targeting settings of the ads.

- 'Captivating' refers to the ad format with the highest average engagement score;
- Age groups are categorized as '18-24', '25-34', '35-44', '45-54', '55-64', and '65+';
- Engagement score measures how well users interact with the ad.

- 'Male gardeners' refers to male users;
- 'Aged between 25 and 45' refers to the age range of the users;
- 'Living in affluent neighborhoods' refers to users in areas with an average income greater than $60,000;
- 'Sown seeds by clicking on ads' refers to users who have clicked on advertisements;
- 'Harvested more than they planted' refers to a return on ad spend (ROAS) greater than 1.
